¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* unto \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*, \w Go|strong="H3212"\w*, get thee \w down|strong="H3381"\w*; for thy \w people|strong="H5971"\w*, which thou \w broughtest|strong="H5927"\w* out of the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*, have \w corrupted|strong="H7843"\w* \add themselves:\add*

And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \w said|strong="H0559"\w* unto \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*, I have \w seen|strong="H7200"\w* this \w people|strong="H5971"\w*, and, behold, it \add is\add* a \w stiffnecked|strong="H7186"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w*:

¶ And \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w* \w turned|strong="H6437"\w*, and went \w down|strong="H3381"\w* from the \w mount|strong="H2022"\w*, and the \w two|strong="H8147"\w* \w tables|strong="H3871"\w* of the \w testimony|strong="H5715"\w* \add were\add* in his \w hand|strong="H3027"\w*: the \w tables|strong="H3871"\w* \add were\add* \w written|strong="H3789"\w* on \w both|strong="H8147"\w* their \w sides|strong="H5676"\w*; on the one side and on the other \add were\add* they \w written|strong="H3789"\w*.

¶ And it came to pass, as soon as he came \w nigh|strong="H7126"\w* unto the \w camp|strong="H4264"\w*, that he \w saw|strong="H7200"\w* the \w calf|strong="H5695"\w*, and the \w dancing|strong="H4246"\w*: and \w Moses’|strong="H4872"\w* \w anger|strong="H0639"\w* waxed \w hot|strong="H2734"\w*, and he \w cast|strong="H7993"\w* the \w tables|strong="H3871"\w* out of his \w hands|strong="H3027"\w*, and \w brake|strong="H7665"\w* them \w beneath|strong="H8478"\w* the \w mount|strong="H2022"\w*.

¶ And when \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w* \w saw|strong="H7200"\w* that the \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \add were\add* \w naked|strong="H6544"\w*; (for \w Aaron|strong="H0175"\w* had made them \w naked|strong="H6544"\w* unto \add their\add* \w shame|strong="H8103"\w* among their \w enemies|strong="H6965"\w*:)\f + \fr 32.25 \ft their enemies: Heb. those that rose up against them\f*

¶ And it came to pass on the \w morrow|strong="H4283"\w*, that \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w* \w said|strong="H0559"\w* unto the \w people|strong="H5971"\w*, Ye have \w sinned|strong="H2398"\w* a \w great|strong="H1419"\w* \w sin|strong="H2401"\w*: and now I will go \w up|strong="H5927"\w* unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; \w peradventure|strong="H0194"\w* I shall make an \w atonement|strong="H3722"\w* \w for|strong="H1157"\w* your \w sin|strong="H2403"\w*.
